{{Taxobox | name = Dinagat gymnure | image = | status = EN | status_system = IUCN3.1 | status_ref = <ref name=iucn>{{cite journal |author=Balete, D. |author2=Tabao, M. |author3=Tabaranza, B. |last-author-amp=yes |title=''Podogymnura aureospinula'' |journal=[[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] |volume=2008 |page=e.T17829A7515155 |publisher=[[IUCN]] |year=2008 |url=http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/17829/0 |doi=10.2305/IUCN.UK.2008.RLTS.T17829A7515155.en |access-date=8 November 2017}}</ref> | regnum = [[Animalia]] | phylum = [[Chordata]] | classis = [[Mammalia]] | ordo = [[Eulipotyphla]] | familia = [[Erinaceidae]] | genus = ''[[Podogymnura]]'' | species = '''''P. aureospinula''''' | binomial = ''Podogymnura aureospinula'' | binomial_authority = [[Lawrence Richard Heaney|Heaney]] & Morgan, 1982 | synonyms = | range_map = Dinagat Gymnure area.png | range_map_caption = Dinagat Gymnure range }}
The '''Dinagat gymnure''' (''Podogymnura aureospinula'') is a species of [[mammal]] in the family [[Erinaceidae]]. It is [[endemic]] to the [[Philippines]].
Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical dry [[forest]]s. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].
