{{Infobox software | name = Giant Virus Finder | logo = | screenshot = | caption = | developer = Csaba Kerepesi | latest release version = | latest preview version = | latest preview date = | operating system = Linux | programming language = [[Perl]], [[Python (programming language)|Python]] | language = [[English language|English]] | genre = [[Bioinformatics]] | license = [[GNU General Public Licence]] | website = http://pitgroup.org/giant-virus-finder }}
The '''Giant Virus Finder''' is a free bioinformatics software for finding [[Girus|giant viruses]] in [[metagenomics|metagenomes]].
== Applications ==
The Giant Virus Finder tool integrates and applies the [http://pitgroup.org/giant-virus-toplist/ Giant Virus Toplist], the list of the largest virus genomes. With the tool, giant viruses were found in diverse habitats, like the [[Great Rann of Kutch]] <ref name="connectome"> {{Cite journal | volume = 161 | issue = 3 | pages = 721–724 | last1 = Kerepesi | first1 = Csaba | last2 = Grolmusz | first2 = Vince | title = Giant Viruses of the Kutch Desert | journal= Archives of Virology | year = 2016 | pmc= | doi=10.1007/s00705-015-2720-8 | pmid= 26666442 | arxiv= 1410.1278 }}</ref> or the [[Mojave Desert]], the [[Prairie]], or the [[Antarctic dry valleys]] .<ref name="kettes"> {{Cite journal | volume = 162 | issue = 6 | pages = 1671 | last1 = Kerepesi | first1 = Csaba | last2 = Grolmusz | first2 = Vince | title = The "Giant Virus Finder" Discovers an Abundance of Giant Viruses in the Antarctic Dry Valleys | journal= Archives of Virology | year = 2017 | pmc= | doi= 10.1007/s00705-017-3286-4 | pmid= 28247094 | arxiv= 1503.05575 }}</ref>
