{{Use British English|date=February 2014}}
{{refimprove|date=January 2013}}

'''''The Investigators''''' was a [[BAFTA]]-nominated<ref>{{cite web|title=The BAFTAs Awards Database|url=http://www.bafta.org/awards-database.html?pageNo=74&sq=factual|accessdate=15 May 2012}}</ref>  children's science program, presented by children, on [[Channel 4]] in [[Great Britain]]. It showed various interesting [[experiments]] from how to blow a [[balloon]] up with [[yeast]] to building [[bridge]]s. Other experiments included on the program were making [[salmon]] flavoured [[ice cream]] and making [[periscopes]].
It aired on Saturday morning.

Presenters included [[Adam Davies (footballer, born 1987)|Adam Davies]], Flo Carson, [[Rhys Williams (footballer)|Rhys Williams]], [[Constance Lound-Mcgowan]], [[John Forster (presenter)|John Forster]], [[Alice Govan]], [[Jay Simpson]], [[Camille St-Omer]] and [[Kevin Jarin]].

